                            <comment id="15501537" author="nbeyer" created="Sun, 18 Sep 2016 19:46:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like &apos;X&apos; has been added to master: &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=commons-lang.git;a=blob;f=src/main/java/org/apache/commons/lang3/time/FastDateParser.java;h=8275ddfd2b5eade34a4a19048c1b0b869d8f1eda;hb=refs/heads/master#l600&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=commons-lang.git;a=blob;f=src/main/java/org/apache/commons/lang3/time/FastDateParser.java;h=8275ddfd2b5eade34a4a19048c1b0b869d8f1eda;hb=refs/heads/master#l600&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15502529" author="britter" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 07:00:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hyukjin.kwon&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hyukjin.kwon&quot;&gt;hyukjin.kwon&lt;/a&gt; which constructor are you using for FastDateFormat? There is no constructor using only a single String parameter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15502559" author="gurwls223" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 07:13:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, I am so sorry. I use &lt;tt&gt;FastDateFormat.getInstance(&quot;yyyy-MM-dd&apos;T&apos;HH:mm:ss.SSSXXX&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt;. It wrote this wrong during testing between &lt;tt&gt;SimpleDateFormat&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;FastDateFormat&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
